\begin_layout Part*
Filtros
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Las señales de entrada a medir, definidas por consigna para el grupo, son:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$x_1(t) = A
\backslash
cdot cos(2
\backslash
pi f_{in} t)$
\end_layout

\end_inset

, con 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$f_{in}=1kHz$
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$x_2(t)$
\end_layout

\end_inset

, siendo esta la extensión periódica de 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$A
\backslash
cdot sin(2
\backslash
pi f_{in} t)$
\end_layout

\end_inset

, con 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$t
\backslash
epsilon[0;3
\backslash
pi]$
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

$x_3(t)$
\end_layout

\end_inset

, siendo esta la extensión periódica de 
\begin_inset ERT
